HOW I WORE IT ⚡️ A new series I’m doing! I will be recreating outfits I see on others and will only use what’s already in my closet. It could be a very loose representation, or an almost exact copy. I am starting with @haileybieber because I love her style. I saw this look on Pinterest and loved it. I knew I already had it all, except the red hat, so I brought in red with my handbag. I mean, Hailey wore it better 😁 but it turned out cute! What do you think? Going to try and do this weekly in hopes that it will inspire you to do the same! It might also get you to try an outfit you wouldn’t normally, because why not have fun with clothes!!

I’m sure you’ve been to @bowoodbyniche for brunch (who hasn’t), but did you know you can now have dinner on their newly renovated garden patio?! 
@bowoodbyniche is located inside Bowood Farms, an urban garden center in the Central West End.
The dinner menu features wood-fired pizza made with house made dough and local, heritage flours along with other delicious entrees, appetizers and desserts. We started out with the trout dip & watermelon for appetizers, for entrees we had the black hawk steak and Strozzapreti, and for dessert we had the tiramisu (which was the best I’ve ever had 😍)‼️
* To view the dinner menu or book a table, visit BowoodByNiche.com or check my stories for a link to book! Pro Tip: @bowoodbyniche now offers complimentary valet during dinner service too! After dinner be sure to walk around the gorgeous garden area 🌸🌺🌼
